{"ts":"2026-06-26T07:58:30.274Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Confirming Clean Code**\n\nI'm pleased to report that the linting process concluded successfully with a clean bill of health. No errors were detected, allowing us to proceed confidently. Next, I'm focusing on crafting the legal and investor relations pages. The goal is a premium, editorial feel that is institutional and strategically styled.\n\n\n**Defining Design Plan**\n\nI've shifted focus to defining a design plan for the four utility pages. I'm starting with a detailed plan for the Privacy Policy page, considering the institutional nature of the document and our commitment to security. Next, I will plan the Terms page.\n\n\n**Designing Secure Pages**\n\nI'm now deep in the design phase for the new pages, specifically targeting CIOs and Chief Compliance Officers. My plan centers on demonstrating secure data practices visually. I'm focusing on a cryptographic shield metaphor—possibly a layered, animated SVG—to represent data isolation. The layout will include a sticky, interactive navigation and premium typographic sections. I am also planning a secure telemetry preview diagram for the dashboard. Interactive elements like micro-hovers and a smooth-scrolling index sidebar will provide a user-friendly experience.\n\n\n**Adapting for Mobile**\n\nI'm now adapting the pages for mobile users. Sidebar navigations will collapse into a horizontal scrollable list or accordion. I'm prioritizing legible text with a perfect vertical rhythm and clean typography across all devices. The `/app/privacy/page.tsx` file is the current target. I've been instructed not to touch the landing page or configuration files.\n\n\\n\\n\n\n**Outlining Terms Strategy**\n\nI've moved on to the Terms of Service. This section will cover compute allocations, API usage, and self-healing SLA mechanisms, setting clear boundaries for developers. I'm exploring a high-availability server grid or consensus network visual metaphor. The layout includes a \"Legal & Compliance\" badge, a sticky navigation similar to the Privacy page, Bento-like cards for compute, usage rules, and SLA recovery, and an SVG schematic for container orchestration.\n\n\n**Defining NDA Workflow**\n\nI'm now outlining the Terms of Service mobile experience and interaction design. Smooth scrolling and hover effects are priorities, and the layout will be linear. I'm focusing on `/app/terms/page.tsx` for these changes, and will maintain focus on the Terms of Service high-availability gateway strategy. I'm also now planning for NDA interaction with a \"Protocol Pipeline\" diagram.\n\n\n**Planning NDA Design**\n\nI'm now focusing on a tabbed or stepped system for the NDA process, demonstrating initiation, cryptographic locking, and audit steps. I plan a refined front-end request form for clients. For mobile, I'm designing a compact vertical layout for the timeline and step cards. I'll modify `/app/nda/page.tsx` and leave the landing page untouched. I've also begun sketching out the Investor Relations page, with a focus on a clean institutional feel.\n\n\n**Formulating Investor Relations**\n\nI'm now deep in the investor relations design. The focus is a high-level capital-allocation schematic, a growth milestones timeline, or a scale-up map. The layout will have a \"Financial Operations\" theme, with a hero SVG depicting capital efficiency. There's also a narrative timeline of company scaling phases, and an \"Institutional Pathways\" grid. A premium CTA section for strategic investors is planned. I'm exploring tabbed sections, and elegant interactive request forms. For mobile, it will be a horizontal scroll grid. I will need to verify Lucide icon package usage.\n\n\n**Implementing Iconography**\n\nI've confirmed the successful installation of `react` and `react-icons`, providing access to a suite of icons, particularly from `lucide-react`. I'm starting to integrate premium SVG graphics and interactive UI components to achieve a robust layout. My focus remains on `/app/privacy/page.tsx`, and I've re-examined the `InnerPageHeroProps` interface for correct utilization.\n\n\n**Refining Privacy Page**\n\nI'm now fully immersed in refining the privacy page. My focus includes adhering to quality rules like premium typography, responsive design with a sticky layout, and a narrative-driven structure. I plan to add an interactive quick-scroll sidebar, a custom SVG for cryptographic architecture, and interactive \"Privacy Level\" badges with micro-interactions. A structured typography layout with an animated background grid will be included as well.\n\n\n**Detailing Privacy Content**\n\nMy immediate task is populating the `/privacy` page, starting with \"Legal & Compliance\" category and a \"Privacy & Data Sovereign Policy\" title, highlighting \"Sovereign.\" I'm also preparing the description on our zero-trust framework. I'll outline the sections: Cryptographic Sandboxing, Model Weight Decoupling, SOC2 Telemetry, and Security Standards. I'll also add a refined contact CTA.\n\n\n"}}
{"ts":"2026-06-26T07:58:30.276Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"editor","toolCallId":"j8g2mf8z","input":{"path":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/app/privacy/page.tsx","new_text":"\"use client\";\n\nimport React, { useState, useEffect } from \"react\";\nimport InnerPageShell from \"@/components/inner-pages/InnerPageShell\";\nimport InnerPageHero from \"@/components/inner-pages/InnerPageHero\";\nimport PremiumCTA from \"@/components/inner-pages/PremiumCTA\";\nimport { Shield, Lock, Eye, CheckCircle, Database, Server, RefreshCw } from \"lucide-react\";\n\nexport default function PrivacyPolicyPage() {\n  const [activeTab, setActiveTab] = useState(\"telemetry\");\n  const [activeSection, setActiveSection] = useState(\"sec-1\");\n\n  const sections = [\n    {\n      id: \"sec-1\",\n      icon: <Shield className=\"w-5 h-5 text-[#E4000F]\" />,\n      title: \"1. Cryptographic Sandboxing & Ingestion Boundaries\",\n      subtitle: \"Absolute tenant isolation for mission-critical enterprise intelligence.\",\n      text: \"At GFF AI, client data ingestion is cryptographically sandboxed in designated local container boundaries. We enforce a physical or logical isolation protocol. No raw text, structured documents, or vector embeddings escape this boundary. Models operating in the Foundry or Factory stage do not transmit telemetry payloads outside your approved virtual private cloud (VPC) configurations.\"\n    },\n    {\n      id: \"sec-2\",\n      icon: <Lock className=\"w-5 h-5 text-[#009DFF]\" />,\n      title: \"2. Model Weight Decoupling & Isolation\",\n      subtitle: \"Securing proprietary logic from global training loops.\",\n      text: \"Your model weights, cognitive adjustments, and system blueprints remain exclusively yours. Unlike generic SaaS providers, GFF AI guarantees that custom adaptations and fine-tuning weights operating in the Garage, Foundry, or Factory stages are completely decoupled. They are never ingested, synthesized, or backpropagated into our public base models, preserving absolute proprietary leverage.\"\n    },\n    {\n      id: \"sec-3\",\n      icon: <Eye className=\"w-5 h-5 text-white\" />,\n      title: \"3. Non-Intrusive Telemetry & Zero-Payload Logging\",\n      subtitle: \"Institutional monitoring focused strictly on system health, not your assets.\",\n      text: \"To power real-time dashboards in the Client Portal, we log structural operational telemetry: CPU loads, active agent dispatcher latency, and token consumption metrics. GFF AI does not log, inspect, or retain prompts, responses, execution contexts, or memory caches. Telemetry datasets are fully anonymized and comply with SOC2 Type II audit specifications.\"\n    },\n    {\n      id: \"sec-4\",\n      icon: <Database className=\"w-5 h-5 text-[#009DFF]\" />,\n      title: \"4. Storage, Retention, and Cryptographic Excision\",\n      subtitle: \"AES-256-GCM standards and instantaneous secure purging.\",\n      text: \"All administrative tokens, sandbox credentials, and secure pipeline configurations are encrypted using AES-256-GCM at rest and TLS 1.3 in transit. Upon termination of a trial or engagement, GFF AI executes an automated Cryptographic Excision protocol. This immediately shreds active sandbox memory registries and zeroizes any persistent cache stores across all multi-tenant nodes.\"\n    },\n    {\n      id: \"sec-5\",\n      icon: <Server className=\"w-5 h-5 text-red-500\" />,\n      title: \"5. Sovereign Regional Deployments & GDPR Compliance\",\n      subtitle: \"Local data locks aligning with global regulatory standards.\",\n      text: \"We host sandbox operations across secure infrastructure nodes globally. Customers can select localized compute lock zones. This ensures that memory buffers, agent interactions, and model routing pipelines never leave specific jurisdictional boundaries, in full compliance with GDPR (Europe), CCPA (California), and local sovereignty mandates.\"\n    }\n  ];\n\n  // Handle active section on scroll\n  useEffect(() => {\n    const handleScroll = () => {\n      const scrollPosition = window.scrollY + 200;\n      for (const sect of sections) {\n        const el = document.getElementById(sect.id);\n        if (el) {\n          const top = el.offsetTop;\n          const height = el.offsetHeight;\n          if (scrollPosition >= top && scrollPosition < top + height) {\n            setActiveSection(sect.id);\n            break;\n          }\n        }\n      }\n    };\n\n    window.addEventListener(\"scroll\", handleScroll);\n    return () => window.removeEventListener(\"scroll\", handleScroll);\n  }, [sections]);\n\n  const scrollToSection = (id: string) => {\n    const el = document.getElementById(id);\n    if (el) {\n      window.scrollTo({\n        top: el.offsetTop - 120,\n        behavior: \"smooth\"\n      });\n      setActiveSection(id);\n    }\n  };\n\n  const simulatorTabs = [\n    {\n      id: \"telemetry\",\n      label: \"System Telemetry Log\",\n      description: \"How our dashboard monitors resource allocation, latency, and throughput transparently without reading data.\",\n      code: `{\n  \"gff_gateway\": \"active\",\n  \"isolated_tenant_id\": \"tenant_0x8f2d9c1\",\n  \"telemetry\": {\n    \"agent_dispatch_latency_ms\": 142.5,\n    \"model_compute_quota_utilized\": \"41.8%\",\n    \"active_dag_nodes\": 8,\n    \"token_throughput_per_sec\": 1240\n  },\n  \"payload_security\": {\n    \"prompt_logging\": \"DISABLED\",\n    \"memory_vector_inspection\": \"MUTED\",\n    \"tls_handshake_state\": \"TLS_1.3_ENCRYPTED\"\n  }\n}`\n    },\n    {\n      id: \"isolation\",\n      label: \"Sandbox Decoupling Flow\",\n      description: \"Ensures that custom cognitive weights do not leak into global base-model repositories.\",\n      code: `/* Sandboxed Data Ingestion Protocol */\n[Input Prompts] \n       │ ──> (Bilateral TLS 1.3 Tunnel)\n       ▼\n[Custom Context Sandbox Boundary]\n       │ ──> Local Vector Index (AES-256 Memory Lock)\n       ▼\n[Decoupled Foundry Model Engine] ──x [Global Base Model] (BLOCK)\n       │\n       ▼\n[Deterministic Agent Action Plan] ──> (Executed via isolated sandbox gateway)`\n    }\n  ];\n\n  return (\n    <InnerPageShell>\n      <InnerPageHero\n        category=\"Legal & Compliance\"\n        title=\"Privacy & Data Sovereign Policy\"\n        highlightedWord=\"Sovereign\"\n        description=\"Learn how GFF AI enforces cryptographic boundaries, strict tenant decoupling, and SOC2-compliant non-intrusive logging to protect enterprise intelligence.\"\n      />\n\n      {/* Main Content Layout */}\n      <div className=\"max-w-[1795px] mx-auto px-6 lg:px-16 pb-24 grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-12 gap-12 relative z-10\">\n        \n        {/* Sticky Left Navigation Index */}\n        <aside className=\"lg:col-span-3 hidden lg:block\">\n          <div className=\"sticky top-[120px] p-6 rounded-[24px] border border-white/5 bg-[#050505]/40 backdrop-blur-[12px] space-y-6\">\n            <div className=\"text-[11px] font-mono uppercase tracking-widest text-white/40\">\n              Document Sections\n            </div>\n            <nav className=\"flex flex-col space-y-2\">\n              {sections.map((sect) => (\n                <button\n                  key={sect.id}\n                  onClick={() => scrollToSection(sect.id)}\n                  className={`flex items-center gap-3 text-left py-2.5 px-3 rounded-lg text-[13px] transition-all ${\n                    activeSection === sect.id\n                      ? \"text-[#009DFF] bg-[#009DFF]/5 font-medium border-l-2 border-[#009DFF]\"\n                      : \"text-white/50 hover:text-white hover:bg-white/5\"\n                  }`}\n                >\n                  {sect.icon}\n                  <span className=\"truncate\">{sect.title.split(\". \")[1]}</span>\n                </button>\n              ))}\n            </nav>\n            <div className=\"pt-6 border-t border-white/5 text-[11px] text-white/40 leading-relaxed\">\n              <span className=\"block font-semibold text-white/60 mb-1\">Last Updated: June 26, 2026</span>\n              This framework serves as our official unilateral privacy architecture blueprint pending bespoke enterprise SLA terms.\n            </div>\n          </div>\n        </aside>\n\n        {/* Dynamic Legal Text Content */}\n        <main className=\"lg:col-span-9 space-y-12\">\n          \n          {/* Custom SVG Architectural Graphic (Design Element 1) */}\n          <div className=\"p-8 rounded-[24px] border border-white/5 bg-gradient-to-b from-[#070709] to-[#010101] overflow-hidden relative group\">\n            <div className=\"absolute top-0 right-0 w-[200px] h-[200px] bg-[#009DFF]/5 rounded-full blur-[50px] pointer-events-none\" />\n            <div className=\"flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-8 items-center\">\n              <div className=\"flex-1 space-y-4\">\n                <div className=\"inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-3 py-1 text-[11px] font-mono tracking-widest text-[#009DFF] border border-[#009DFF]/20 bg-[#009DFF]/5 rounded-full uppercase\">\n                  <RefreshCw className=\"w-3.5 h-3.5 animate-spin\" /> Zero-Trust Routing Schema\n                </div>\n                <h3 className=\"text-[20px] font-semibold text-white tracking-tight\">\n                  Cryptographic Data Isolation Architecture\n                </h3>\n                <p className=\"text-white/60 text-[13px] font-light leading-[1.6]\">\n                  This structural blueprint highlights how multi-agent data feeds enter GFF AI routers, are cryptographically isolated within AES-256 containers, and interface with the decoupled client cognitive engine without touching external nodes.\n                </p>\n              </div>\n              <div className=\"w-full md:w-[280px] h-[180px] relative flex items-center justify-center border border-white/5 rounded-xl bg-black/50 overflow-hidden\">\n                <svg className=\"w-full h-full p-4\" viewBox=\"0 0 280 180\" fill=\"none\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\">\n                  {/* Grid Lines */}\n                  <path d=\"M0 30 H280 M0 90 H280 M0 150 H280 M60 0 V180 M140 0 V180 M220 0 V180\" stroke=\"white\" strokeWidth=\"0.5\" className=\"opacity-5\" strokeDasharray=\"3 3\" />\n                  \n                  {/* Left node (Data Input) */}\n                  <rect x=\"15\" y=\"70\" width=\"40\" height=\"40\" rx=\"6\" fill=\"#0c0c0e\" stroke=\"url(#strokeGrad)\" strokeWidth=\"1\" />\n                  <text x=\"35\" y=\"94\" textAnchor=\"middle\" fill=\"white\" fontSize=\"9\" fontFamily=\"monospace\" opacity=\"0.8\">DATA</text>\n\n                  {/* Dynamic path lines */}\n                  <path d=\"M55 90 H105\" stroke=\"url(#strokeGrad)\" strokeWidth=\"1.5\" strokeDasharray=\"4 2\" className=\"animate-[dash_2s_linear_infinite]\" />\n                  \n                  {/* Mid secure core (Cryptographic Sandbox) */}\n                  <rect x=\"105\" y=\"55\" width=\"70\" height=\"70\" rx=\"10\" fill=\"#030304\" stroke=\"#009DFF\" strokeWidth=\"1.5\" className=\"shadow-lg shadow-[#009DFF]/20\" />\n                  <circle cx=\"140\" cy=\"90\" r=\"14\" fill=\"#009DFF\" fillOpacity=\"0.1\" />\n                  <path d=\"M140 82 V98 M132 90 H148\" stroke=\"#009DFF\" strokeWidth=\"1.5\" />\n                  <text x=\"140\" y=\"112\" textAnchor=\"middle\" fill=\"#009DFF\" fontSize=\"7\" fontFamily=\"monospace\" fontWeight=\"bold\">SANDBOX</text>\n\n                  {/* Right node (Decoupled Output) */}\n                  <path d=\"M175 90 H225\" stroke=\"url(#strokeGrad)\" strokeWidth=\"1.5\" strokeDasharray=\"4 2\" />\n                  <rect x=\"225\" y=\"70\" width=\"40\" height=\"40\" rx=\"6\" fill=\"#0c0c0e\" stroke=\"url(#strokeGrad)\" strokeWidth=\"1\" />\n                  <text x=\"245\" y=\"94\" textAnchor=\"middle\" fill=\"white\" fontSize=\"9\" fontFamily=\"monospace\" opacity=\"0.8\">MODEL</text>\n\n                  <defs>\n                    <linearGradient id=\"strokeGrad\" x1=\"0\" y1=\"0\" x2=\"280\" y2=\"180\" gradientUnits=\"userSpaceOnUse\">\n                      <stop stopColor=\"#E4000F\" />\n                      <stop offset=\"1\" stopColor=\"#009DFF\" />\n                    </linearGradient>\n                  </defs>\n                </svg>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n          </div>\n\n          {/* Legal Clauses List with Custom Typography */}\n          <div className=\"space-y-12\">\n            {sections.map((sect) => (\n              <section\n                key={sect.id}\n                id={sect.id}\n                className=\"scroll-mt-[150px] p-8 rounded-[24px] border border-white/5 bg-[#050505]/40 backdrop-blur-[12px] space-y-4 hover:border-white/10 transition-all duration-300\"\n              >\n                <div className=\"flex items-center gap-4\">\n                  <div className=\"p-2.5 rounded-xl bg-white/5 border border-white/10\">\n                    {sect.icon}\n                  </div>\n                  <div>\n                    <h2 className=\"text-[18px] sm:text-[20px] font-semibold text-white tracking-tight\">{sect.title}</h2>\n                    <p className=\"text-[12px] text-white/40 tracking-wider uppercase font-mono mt-0.5\">{sect.subtitle}</p>\n                  </div>\n                </div>\n                <div className=\"pt-4 border-t border-white/5 text-white/70 text-[14px] leading-[1.7] font-light space-y-4\">\n                  <p>{sect.text}</p>\n                  <p className=\"text-[13px] text-white/40 italic\">\n                    Note: Complete data routing specifications and customer-specific legal warranties are subject to execute under the bilateral Master Services Agreement (MSA).\n                  </p>\n                </div>\n              </section>\n            ))}\n          </div>\n\n          {/* Interactive Trust/Compliance Simulator (Design Element 2) */}\n          <section className=\"p-8 rounded-[24px] border border-white/5 bg-[#050505]/60 backdrop-blur-[12px] space-y-6\">\n            <div className=\"space-y-2\">\n              <span className=\"px-3 py-1 text-[10px] font-mono tracking-widest text-[#009DFF] border border-[#009DFF]/20 bg-[#009DFF]/5 rounded-full uppercase\">\n                Interactive Inspector\n              </span>\n              <h3 className=\"text-[20px] font-semibold text-white tracking-tight\">Trust & Logging Transparency Console</h3>\n              <p className=\"text-white/60 text-[14px] font-light leading-relaxed\">\n                Toggle through our system modules to inspect the structural telemetry schemas we transmit versus our complete isolation flow.\n              </p>\n            </div>\n\n            <div className=\"flex border-b border-white/5\">\n              {simulatorTabs.map((tab) => (\n                <button\n                  key={tab.id}\n                  onClick={() => setActiveTab(tab.id)}\n                  className={`py-3 px-6 text-[13px] font-medium transition-all relative ${\n                    activeTab === tab.id\n                      ? \"text-white font-semibold\"\n                      : \"text-white/40 hover:text-white/80\"\n                  }`}\n                >\n                  {tab.label}\n                  {activeTab === tab.id && (\n                    <div className=\"absolute bottom-0 left-0 right-0 h-[2px] bg-gradient-to-r from-[#E4000F] to-[#009DFF]\" />\n                  )}\n                </button>\n              ))}\n            </div>\n\n            <div className=\"space-y-4\">\n              <p className=\"text-[13px] text-white/70 font-light italic\">\n                {simulatorTabs.find((t) => t.id === activeTab)?.description}\n              </p>\n              <pre className=\"p-5 rounded-xl border border-white/5 bg-[#030304] text-[12px] font-mono text-white/80 overflow-x-auto leading-[1.6]\">\n                <code>{simulatorTabs.find((t) => t.id === activeTab)?.code}</code>\n              </pre>\n            </div>\n          </section>\n\n          {/* Premium Contact Call-to-Action (Design Element 3) */}\n          <PremiumCTA\n            title=\"Have Custom Governance & Data Location Requirements?\"\n            description=\"Our specialized systems integration team regularly assists global banks, health tech providers, and public institutions with high-security deployment blueprints.\"\n            primaryLabel=\"Contact Compliance Desk\"\n            primaryHref=\"/contact?pathway=governance\"\n            secondaryLabel=\"View Architectural Library\"\n            secondaryHref=\"/resources/architecture-library\"\n          />\n\n        </main>\n      </div>\n    </InnerPageShell>\n  );\n}\n"}}}
